The paper discusses ablation studies in artificial neural networks (ANNs) and their ability to investigate the inner representations of these networks. This topic falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV), as the paper specifically examines two benchmark datasets from the computer vision domain. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of network robustness, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL).
